      "id": "626700557200289",
      "score": 5,
      "review_title": "Fun and promising but room for improveme",
      "review_description": "Room Invaders is definitely a fun and entertaining experience. The concept is creative and defending Zooky in mixed reality is a blast. It’s the kind of game that makes you move and play for hours that said there's still room to grow\n\nIt could really benefit from boss fights or more stage variety to keep the action fresh. The bat physics need some refinement since landing hits isn’t always smooth. Picking up health items by mistake when trying to grab weapons happens a lot too which can break the rhythm\n\nA progress tracker for achievements would be super helpful and there’s also a recurring bug where an error pops up and kicks you from the session\n\nFor future updates it’d be awesome to earn intergalactic coins to upgrade your weapons or summon minions to help with enemy waves. And being able to customize weapons or Zooky with fun skins would add a cool layer of personality. Imagine defending the galaxy with a flaming bat and a space baby in shades 😎\n\nOverall it’s a solid game with a lot of potential. I’m excited to see how it evolves and it’s definitely worth playing and keeping an eye on\n\nIf you get the chance to try it don’t let it slip through your alien-proof gloves. It’s fun fast chaotic and full of charm 🛸\n\nZooky needs you\nThe galaxy needs you\n\n🛡️ Suit up defender it’s time to turn your living room into a battleground",
      "date": 1749168354,
      "review_helpful_count": 7,
      "author_display_name": "Sammy.05",
      "author_alias": "Sammy.05",
      "developer_response": null
    },
